casebody.data:
UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Miguel Angel ZAMORA ALONZO, also known as Miguel Angel Zamora Alonso, Defendant-Appellant. No. 11-51012

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. June 19, 2012. Joseph H. Gay, Jr., Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, San Antonio, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Cori Ann Harbour-Valdez, Harbour Law Firm, P.C., El Paso, TX, for Defendant-Appellant.

Before DAVIS, STEWART, and PRADO, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM: *

The attorney appointed to represent Miguel Angel Zamora Alonzo has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967), and United States v. Flores, 632 F.3d 229 (5th Cir.2011). Zamora Alonzo has not filed a response. We have reviewed counsel’s brief and the relevant portions of the record reflected therein. *377We concur with counsel’s assessment that the appeal presents no nonfrivolous issue for appellate review. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
